nt WordPress Loop and shouldn't be used more than&#10;once. This must not be used within the WordPress Loop.&#10;&#10;@since 1.5.0&#10;@uses $wp_query&#10;&#10;@param string $query&#10;@return array List of posts" ilk="function" line="89" lineend="92" name="query_posts" returns="array" signature="array query_posts(string $query)"><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="89" name="query" /></scope><scope doc="Destroy the previous query and set up a new query.&#10;&#10;This should be used after {@link query_posts()} and before another {@link&#10;query_posts()}. This will remove obscure bugs that occur when the previous&#10;wp_query object is not destroyed properly before another is set up.&#10;&#10;@since 2.3.0&#10;@uses $wp_query" ilk="function" line="104" lineend="107" name="wp_reset_query" signature="wp_reset_query()" /><scope doc="After looping through a separate query, this function restores&#10;the $post global to the current post in the main query&#10;&#10;@since 3.0.0&#10;@uses $wp_query" ilk="function" line="116" lineend="122" name="wp_reset_postdata" signature="wp_reset_postdata()"><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="117" name="wp_query" /></scope><scope doc="Is the query for an existing archive page?&#10;&#10;Month, Year, Category, Author, Post Type archive...&#10;&#10;@see WP_Query::is_archive()&#10;@since 1.5.0&#10;@uses $wp_query&#10;&#10;@return bool" ilk="function" line="139" lineend="148" name="is_archive" returns="bool" signature="bool is_archive()"><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="140" name="wp_query" /></scope><scope doc="Is the query for an existing post type archive page?&#10;&#10;@see WP_Query::is_post_type_archive()&#10;@since 3.1.0&#10;@uses $wp_query&#10;&#10;@param mixed $post_types Optional. Post type or array of posts types to check against.&#10;@return bool" ilk="function" line="160" lineend="169" name="is_post_type_archive" returns="bool" signature="bool is_post_type_archive(mixed $post_types = '')"><var